{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841880976,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786cab650017ev61JUQ6Jmo0F","messageID":"msg_d786c8def001Zz9Ruswe6IK5bP","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-afd2d8ff7b6a44339bef380bdf05264c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775841880964,"end":1775841880974}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841880980,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786ca429001qo6rVeYYxRBSaf","messageID":"msg_d786c8def001Zz9Ruswe6IK5bP","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-59bce71f930d4cf9b96bd73ef9e5768c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775841880958,"end":1775841880978}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841880995,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786ca7e5001hsH7omeMhXk9Tv","messageID":"msg_d786c8def001Zz9Ruswe6IK5bP","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-52359f04bae844789b1ead4b1fdb3cfe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/apis` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 定义 CRD 共享类型和常量，供 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter CRD 使用。API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`。\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: 共享类型和常量定义遵循 Kubernetes API conventions：\n20: - 类型定义使用 `kubebuilder` markers 生成 OpenAPI schema\n21: - 常量使用统一命名规范（LabelKey*, AnnotationKey*, ConditionType*）\n22: - 默认值常量供 controller 使用\n23: - 所有定义位于 `shared_types.go`，便于集中管理\n24: \n25: ### Dependencies\n26: \n27: | Package | Purpose |\n28: |---------|---------|\n29: | (无外部依赖) | 共享类型为基础定义 |\n30: \n31: ### Controller-gen Markers\n32: \n33: | Marker | Applied to | Purpose |\n34: |--------|------------|---------|\n35: | `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum` | ProtocolType, AuthModeType | 枚举验证 |\n36: | `+kubebuilder:default` | TargetPort.Protocol | 默认值 |\n37: \n38: ## Data Structures\n39: \n40: ### Shared Types\n41: \n42: #### ProtocolType\n43: \n44: ```go\n45: // ProtocolType defines the protocol for a target port.\n46: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n47: type ProtocolType string\n48: \n49: const (\n50:     // ProtocolTypeHTTP indicates HTTP protocol.\n51:     ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n52:     // ProtocolTypeHTTPS indicates HTTPS protocol.\n53:     ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n54: )\n55: ```\n56: \n57: #### AuthModeType\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: // AuthModeType defines the authentication mode for a CodeInterpreter.\n61: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n62: type AuthModeType string\n63: \n64: const (\n65:     // AuthModePicoD indicates pico authentication mode.\n66:     AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n67:     // AuthModeNone indicates no authentication.\n68:     AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n69: )\n70: ```\n71: \n72: #### TargetPort\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: // TargetPort defines a network port configuration for exposing sandbox services.\n76: type TargetPort struct {\n77:     // PathPrefix is the URL path prefix for routing to this port.\n78:     // +optional\n79:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n80: \n81:     // Name is a human-readable name for this port.\n82:     // +optional\n83:     Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n84: \n85:     // Port is the container port number to expose.\n86:     Port uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n87: \n88:     // Protocol specifies the protocol for this port (HTTP or HTTPS).\n89:     // +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n90:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n91:     Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Constants\n96: \n97: #### Label Constants\n98: \n99: Labels 用于标识沙箱资源的元数据，遵循 `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/<key>` 格式：\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: const (\n103:     // LabelKeyOwnerRuntime indicates the owning AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter name.\n104:     LabelKeyOwnerRuntime = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime\"\n105: \n106:     // LabelKeyOwnerKind indicates the owning CRD kind (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter).\n107:     LabelKeyOwnerKind = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind\"\n108: \n109:     // LabelKeySessionID indicates the active session identifier.\n110:     LabelKeySessionID = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id\"\n111: \n112:     // LabelKeySandboxType indicates the sandbox type (agent/code-interpreter).\n113:     LabelKeySandboxType = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type\"\n114: \n115:     // LabelKeySandboxTypeAgent indicates an agent sandbox.\n116:     LabelKeySandboxTypeAgent = \"agent\"\n117: \n118:     // LabelKeySandboxTypeCodeInterpreter indicates a code interpreter sandbox.\n119:     LabelKeySandboxTypeCodeInterpreter = \"code-interpreter\"\n120: )\n121: ```\n122: \n123: #### Annotation Constants\n124: \n125: Annotations 用于存储运行时配置和状态信息：\n126: \n127: ```go\n128: const (\n129:     // AnnotationKeyAuthMode stores the authentication mode for the sandbox.\n130:     AnnotationKeyAuthMode = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode\"\n131: \n132:     // AnnotationKeySessionStart stores the session start timestamp.\n133:     AnnotationKeySessionStart = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start\"\n134: \n135:     // AnnotationKeySessionEnd stores the session end timestamp.\n136:     AnnotationKeySessionEnd = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end\"\n137: \n138:     // AnnotationKeyLastActivity stores the last activity timestamp.\n139:     AnnotationKeyLastActivity = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n140: \n141:     // AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember indicates if pod is part of warm pool.\n142:     AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member\"\n143: )\n144: ```\n145: \n146: #### Condition Type Constants\n147: \n148: Condition types 用于 status.conditions 数组，遵循 Kubernetes Condition pattern：\n149: \n150: ```go\n151: const (\n152:     // ConditionTypeReady indicates the runtime is ready to accept sessions.\n153:     ConditionTypeReady = \"Ready\"\n154: \n155:     // ConditionTypeAvailable indicates the runtime is available for use.\n156:     ConditionTypeAvailable = \"Available\"\n157: \n158:     // ConditionTypeProgressing indicates the runtime is being created/updated.\n159:     ConditionTypeProgressing = \"Progressing\"\n160: \n161:     // ConditionTypeDegraded indicates the runtime is in a degraded state.\n162:     ConditionTypeDegraded = \"Degraded\"\n163: \n164:     // ConditionTypeSessionActive indicates an active session is running.\n165:     ConditionTypeSessionActive = \"SessionActive\"\n166: )\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### Condition Reason Constants\n170: \n171: Condition reasons 描述 condition 状态变化的原因：\n172: \n173: ```go\n174: const (\n175:     // ConditionReasonRunning indicates the runtime is running normally.\n176:     ConditionReasonRunning = \"Running\"\n177: \n178:     // ConditionReasonCreating indicates the runtime is being created.\n179:     ConditionReasonCreating = \"Creating\"\n180: \n181:     // ConditionReasonUpdating indicates the runtime is being updated.\n182:     ConditionReasonUpdating = \"Updating\"\n183: \n184:     // ConditionReasonDeleting indicates the runtime is being deleted.\n185:     ConditionReasonDeleting = \"Deleting\"\n186: \n187:     // ConditionReasonError indicates an error occurred.\n188:     ConditionReasonError = \"Error\"\n189: \n190:     // ConditionReasonTimeout indicates a timeout occurred.\n191:     ConditionReasonTimeout = \"Timeout\"\n192: \n193:     // ConditionReasonSessionStarted indicates a session has started.\n194:     ConditionReasonSessionStarted = \"SessionStarted\"\n195: \n196:     // ConditionReasonSessionEnded indicates a session has ended.\n197:     ConditionReasonSessionEnded = \"SessionEnded\"\n198: \n199:     // ConditionReasonIdleTimeout indicates session ended due to idle timeout.\n200:     ConditionReasonIdleTimeout = \"IdleTimeout\"\n201: \n202:     // ConditionReasonMaxDurationReached indicates session ended due to max duration.\n203:     ConditionReasonMaxDurationReached = \"MaxDurationReached\"\n204: )\n205: ```\n206: \n207: #### Default Value Constants\n208: \n209: 默认值常量供 controller 初始化配置使用：\n210: \n211: ```go\n212: const (\n213:     // DefaultSessionTimeout is the default idle session timeout (15 minutes).\n214:     DefaultSessionTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n215: \n216:     // DefaultMaxSessionDuration is the default maximum session duration (8 hours).\n217:     DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n218: \n219:     // DefaultWarmPoolSize is the default warm pool size for CodeInterpreter.\n220:     DefaultWarmPoolSize = 0\n221: \n222:     // DefaultAuthMode is the default authentication mode.\n223:     DefaultAuthMode = AuthModePicoD\n224: \n225:     // DefaultProtocol is the default protocol for TargetPort.\n226:     DefaultProtocol = ProtocolTypeHTTP\n227: )\n228: ```\n229: \n230: ## API Contracts\n231: \n232: ### Label Contract\n233: \n234: | Label Key | Value Format | Applied To |\n235: |-----------|--------------|------------|\n236: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | CR name | Pod, Service |\n237: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `AgentRuntime` / `CodeInterpreter` | Pod, Service |\n238: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | UUID | Pod (active session) |\n239: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `agent` / `code-interpreter` | Pod |\n240: \n241: ### Annotation Contract\n242: \n243: | Annotation Key | Value Format | Applied To |\n244: |-----------------|--------------|------------|\n245: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` | `picod` / `none` | Pod |\n246: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` | RFC3339 timestamp | Pod |\n247: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | RFC3339 timestamp | Pod |\n248: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | RFC3339 timestamp | Pod |\n249: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` | `true` / `false` | Pod |\n250: \n251: ### Condition Contract\n252: \n253: | Condition Type | Meaning | True Condition |\n254: |-----------------|---------|----------------|\n255: | `Ready` | Runtime ready for sessions | Pod running, no errors |\n256: | `Available` | Runtime available | Ready + healthy |\n257: | `Progressing` | Runtime being modified | Creation/update in progress |\n258: | `Degraded` | Runtime in degraded state | Errors present |\n259: | `SessionActive` | Session running | Pod has active session |\n260: \n261: ## Error Handling\n262: \n263: ### Validation Errors\n264: \n265: | Error Type | Trigger | Response |\n266: |------------|---------|----------|\n267: | Invalid ProtocolType | Value not `HTTP`/`HTTPS` | API server rejects with 400 |\n268: | Invalid AuthModeType | Value not `picod`/`none` | API server rejects with 400 |\n269: | Missing required Port | Port field empty | API server rejects with 400 |\n270: | Invalid port number | Port > 65535 | Controller webhook rejects |\n271: \n272: ### Controller Error Handling\n273: \n274: | Error Type | Handling |\n275: |------------|----------|\n276: | Label/Annotation conflict | Log warning, use CR-specified value |\n277: | Condition update failure | Retry with exponential backoff |\n278: | Default value override | Use CR spec value if specified |\n279: \n280: ## Testing Strategy\n281: \n282: ### Unit Tests\n283: \n284: | Test Category | Coverage |\n285: |---------------|----------|\n286: | Enum constants | Verify all enum values match expected strings |\n287: | DeepCopy | TargetPort.DeepCopy creates independent copy |\n288: | JSON serialization | TargetPort JSON tags correct (camelCase) |\n289: | Default values | Verify default constants match spec defaults |\n290: \n291: ### Test Cases\n292: \n293: ```go\n294: func TestProtocolTypeConstants(t *testing.T) {\n295:     tests := []struct {\n296:         name     string\n297:         constant ProtocolType\n298:         expected string\n299:     }{\n300:         {\"HTTP\", ProtocolTypeHTTP, \"HTTP\"},\n301:         {\"HTTPS\", ProtocolTypeHTTPS, \"HTTPS\"},\n302:     }\n303:     for _, tt := range tests {\n304:         if tt.constant != tt.expected {\n305:             t.Errorf(\"%s: expected %s, got %s\", tt.name, tt.expected, tt.constant)\n306:         }\n307:     }\n308: }\n309: \n310: func TestAuthModeTypeConstants(t *testing.T) {\n311:     tests := []struct {\n312:         name     string\n313:         constant AuthModeType\n314:         expected string\n315:     }{\n316:         {\"PicoD\", AuthModePicoD, \"picod\"},\n317:         {\"None\", AuthModeNone, \"none\"},\n318:     }\n319:     for _, tt := range tests {\n320:         if tt.constant != tt.expected {\n321:             t.Errorf(\"%s: expected %s, got %s\", tt.name, tt.expected, tt.constant)\n322:         }\n323:     }\n324: }\n325: \n326: func TestTargetPortDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n327:     original := &TargetPort{\n328:         PathPrefix: \"/api\",\n329:         Name:       \"api\",\n330:         Port:       8080,\n331:         Protocol:   ProtocolTypeHTTP,\n332:     }\n333:     copy := original.DeepCopy()\n334:     \n335:     if copy == original {\n336:         t.Error(\"DeepCopy returned same pointer\")\n337:     }\n338:     if copy.PathPrefix != original.PathPrefix {\n339:         t.Error(\"PathPrefix not copied correctly\")\n340:     }\n341:     \n342:     copy.PathPrefix = \"/modified\"\n343:     if original.PathPrefix == \"/modified\" {\n344:         t.Error(\"DeepCopy is not deep\")\n345:     }\n346: }\n347: \n348: func TestTargetPortJSONSerialization(t *testing.T) {\n349:     tp := TargetPort{\n350:         PathPrefix: \"/api\",\n351:         Name:       \"api\",\n352:         Port:       8080,\n353:         Protocol:   ProtocolTypeHTTP,\n354:     }\n355:     data, err := json.Marshal(tp)\n356:     if err != nil {\n357:         t.Fatalf(\"marshal failed: %v\", err)\n358:     }\n359:     expected := `{\"pathPrefix\":\"/api\",\"name\":\"api\",\"port\":8080,\"protocol\":\"HTTP\"}`\n360:     if string(data) != expected {\n361:         t.Errorf(\"expected %s, got %s\", expected, string(data))\n362:     }\n363: }\n364: \n365: func TestLabelConstants(t *testing.T) {\n366:     if LabelKeyOwnerRuntime != \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime\" {\n367:         t.Error(\"LabelKeyOwnerRuntime mismatch\")\n368:     }\n369:     if LabelKeySessionID != \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id\" {\n370:         t.Error(\"LabelKeySessionID mismatch\")\n371:     }\n372: }\n373: \n374: func TestConditionTypeConstants(t *testing.T) {\n375:     if ConditionTypeReady != \"Ready\" {\n376:         t.Error(\"ConditionTypeReady mismatch\")\n377:     }\n378:     if ConditionTypeAvailable != \"Available\" {\n379:         t.Error(\"ConditionTypeAvailable mismatch\")\n380:     }\n381: }\n382: \n383: func TestDefaultConstants(t *testing.T) {\n384:     if DefaultSessionTimeout != 15*time.Minute {\n385:         t.Error(\"DefaultSessionTimeout mismatch\")\n386:     }\n387:     if DefaultMaxSessionDuration != 8*time.Hour {\n388:         t.Error(\"DefaultMaxSessionDuration mismatch\")\n389:     }\n390:     if DefaultAuthMode != AuthModePicoD {\n391:         t.Error(\"DefaultAuthMode mismatch\")\n392:     }\n393:     if DefaultProtocol != ProtocolTypeHTTP {\n394:         t.Error(\"DefaultProtocol mismatch\")\n395:     }\n396: }\n397: ```\n398: \n399: ### Integration Tests\n400: \n401: - Verify labels/annotations applied to pods match constant definitions\n402: - Verify conditions in CRD status use defined type constants\n403: - Verify CRD YAML generation includes enum validation\n404: \n405: ## File Structure\n406: \n407: ```\n408: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n409:   shared_types.go      — 共享类型、枚举、常量定义\n410:   zz_generated.deepcopy.go — DeepCopy 方法（由 controller-gen 生成）\n411:   types_test.go        — 单元测试\n412: ```\n413: \n414: ### shared_types.go Structure\n415: \n416: ```go\n417: package v1alpha1\n418: \n419: import \"time\"\n420: \n421: // ============================================================================\n422: // Type Definitions\n423: // ============================================================================\n424: \n425: type ProtocolType string\n426: const (\n427:     ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n428:     ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n429: )\n430: \n431: type AuthModeType string\n432: const (\n433:     AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n434:     AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n435: )\n436: \n437: type TargetPort struct {\n438:     PathPrefix string      `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n439:     Name       string      `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n440:     Port       uint32      `json:\"port\"`\n441:     Protocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n442: }\n443: \n444: // ============================================================================\n445: // Label Constants\n446: // ============================================================================\n447: \n448: const (\n449:     LabelKeyOwnerRuntime     = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime\"\n450:     LabelKeyOwnerKind        = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind\"\n451:     LabelKeySessionID        = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id\"\n452:     LabelKeySandboxType      = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type\"\n453:     LabelKeySandboxTypeAgent = \"agent\"\n454:     LabelKeySandboxTypeCodeInterpreter = \"code-interpreter\"\n455: )\n456: \n457: // ============================================================================\n458: // Annotation Constants\n459: // ============================================================================\n460: \n461: const (\n462:     AnnotationKeyAuthMode       = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode\"\n463:     AnnotationKeySessionStart   = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start\"\n464:     AnnotationKeySessionEnd     = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end\"\n465:     AnnotationKeyLastActivity   = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n466:     AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member\"\n467: )\n468: \n469: // ============================================================================\n470: // Condition Constants\n471: // ============================================================================\n472: \n473: const (\n474:     ConditionTypeReady        = \"Ready\"\n475:     ConditionTypeAvailable    = \"Available\"\n476:     ConditionTypeProgressing  = \"Progressing\"\n477:     ConditionTypeDegraded     = \"Degraded\"\n478:     ConditionTypeSessionActive = \"SessionActive\"\n479: )\n480: \n481: const (\n482:     ConditionReasonRunning            = \"Running\"\n483:     ConditionReasonCreating           = \"Creating\"\n484:     ConditionReasonUpdating           = \"Updating\"\n485:     ConditionReasonDeleting           = \"Deleting\"\n486:     ConditionReasonError              = \"Error\"\n487:     ConditionReasonTimeout            = \"Timeout\"\n488:     ConditionReasonSessionStarted     = \"SessionStarted\"\n489:     ConditionReasonSessionEnded       = \"SessionEnded\"\n490:     ConditionReasonIdleTimeout        = \"IdleTimeout\"\n491:     ConditionReasonMaxDurationReached = \"MaxDurationReached\"\n492: )\n493: \n494: // ============================================================================\n495: // Default Value Constants\n496: // ============================================================================\n497: \n498: const (\n499:     DefaultSessionTimeout     = 15 * time.Minute\n500:     DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n501:     DefaultWarmPoolSize       = 0\n502: )\n503: \n504: var (\n505:     DefaultAuthMode  = AuthModePicoD\n506:     DefaultProtocol  = ProtocolTypeHTTP\n507: )\n508: ```\n509: \n510: ## Generation Commands\n511: \n512: | Command | Output |\n513: |---------|--------|\n514: | `make generate` | DeepCopy code in `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` |\n515: | `go build ./pkg/apis/...` | Compile verification |\n516: | `go test ./pkg/apis/...` | Unit test execution |\n517: \n518: ## References\n519: \n520: - Source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n521: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n522: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n523: - AR-001 Design: `changes/AR-001/design.md`\n524: - AR-002 Design: `changes/AR-002/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 524 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 |\n| Module | `pkg/apis` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n定义 CRD 共享类型和常量，供 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter CRD 使用。API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n共享类型和常量定义遵循 Kubernetes API conventions：\n- 类型定义使用 `kubebuilder` markers 生成 OpenAPI schema","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/design.md","time":{"start":1775841880961,"end":1775841880992}}}}
