{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842084836,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786fc7b4001k9NyhFre3iZ6Mi","messageID":"msg_d786fa8e50011gOp6IZ9ulC6t3","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-3758d6c01511462baacfb8a33833897f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md","newString":"## References\n\n- chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n- Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n- Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- client-go: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- AgentRuntime types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n- CodeInterpreter types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- Shared types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n- AR-003 Design: `changes/AR-003/design.md`","oldString":"## References\n\n- chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n- Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n- Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md\n@@ -689,5 +689,10 @@\n ## References\n \n - chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n - Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n-- Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n+- client-go: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n+- AgentRuntime types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n+- CodeInterpreter types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n+- Shared types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n+- AR-003 Design: `changes/AR-003/design.md`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md","before":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，提供 RESTful API 基础设施、中间件架构、生命周期管理。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\ncmd/workload-manager/\n    └── main.go                    — 入口，调用 pkg/workloadmanager\npkg/workloadmanager/\n    ├── server.go                  — HTTPServer 核心实现\n    ├── router.go                  — 路由配置与路由组\n    ├── config.go                  — 配置结构体\n    ├── types.go                   — 公共类型定义\n    ├── doc.go                     — 包文档\n    ├── handlers/\n    │   ├── handler.go             — Handler 接口\n    │   └── health.go              — 健康检查实现\n    └── middleware/\n        ├── logging.go             — 请求日志中间件\n        ├── recovery.go            — Panic 恢复中间件\n        └── cors.go                — CORS 中间件\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Client Integration\n\nWorkloadManager 使用 `client-go` 与 Kubernetes API 交互:\n\n| Client | API Group | Resource | Purpose |\n|--------|-----------|----------|---------|\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `agentruntimes` | 管理 AgentRuntime CR |\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `codeinterpreters` | 管理 CodeInterpreter CR |\n\nClient construction pattern:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    versioned \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n)\n\nfunc NewKubernetesClient(config *rest.Config) (versioned.Interface, error) {\n    return versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n}\n```\n\nTyped client interfaces:\n\n```go\ntype RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n    CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `net/http` | 标准库 HTTP 服务器 |\n| `context` | 请求上下文 |\n| `sync` | 并发控制（优雅关闭） |\n| `os/signal` | 信号处理 |\n| `time` | 超时配置 |\n| `encoding/json` | JSON 序列化 |\n| `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP 路由器 |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/rest` | Kubernetes REST 配置 |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | 生成的 typed client |\n\n### Router Library Selection\n\n**决策**: 使用 `go-chi/chi` v5\n\n| Aspect | Rationale |\n|--------|-----------|\n| 零外部依赖 | 仅依赖 Go 标准库 |\n| 兼容 net/http | 可使用所有标准库中间件 |\n| 路由分组 | 支持路由组与中间件作用域 |\n| 性能 | 足够优秀（参考 benchmark） |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### server.go\n\n```go\ntype HTTPServer struct {\n    server   *http.Server\n    router   chi.Router\n    config   Config\n    handlers map[string]Handler\n    logger   Logger\n    stopCh   chan struct{}\n}\n\nfunc NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger) *HTTPServer {\n    return &HTTPServer{\n        server:   &http.Server{Addr: cfg.Addr},\n        router:   chi.NewRouter(),\n        config:   cfg,\n        handlers: make(map[string]Handler),\n        logger:   logger,\n        stopCh:   make(chan struct{}),\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) Start() <-chan error {\n    errCh := make(chan error, 1)\n    s.server.ReadTimeout = s.config.ReadTimeout\n    s.server.WriteTimeout = s.config.WriteTimeout\n    s.server.IdleTimeout = s.config.IdleTimeout\n    go func() {\n        if err := s.server.ListenAndServe(); err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n            errCh <- err\n        }\n    }()\n    return errCh\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) Stop(ctx context.Context) error {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, s.config.ShutdownTimeout)\n    defer cancel()\n    err := s.server.Shutdown(ctx)\n    close(s.stopCh)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) GracefulShutdown() {\n    sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n    go func() {\n        <-sigCh\n        ctx := context.Background()\n        s.Stop(ctx)\n    }()\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler) {\n    s.handlers[name] = h\n    h.Register(s.router)\n}\n```\n\n### config.go\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Addr              string        // 监听地址，如 \":8080\"\n    ReadTimeout       time.Duration // 读超时\n    WriteTimeout      time.Duration // 写超时\n    IdleTimeout       time.Duration // 空闲连接超时\n    ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration // 优雅关闭超时\n    EnableHealthz     bool          // 是否启用健康检查\n    EnableReadyz      bool          // 是否启用就绪探针\n}\n\nfunc DefaultConfig() Config {\n    return Config{\n        Addr:            \":8080\",\n        ReadTimeout:     15 * time.Second,\n        WriteTimeout:    15 * time.Second,\n        IdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n        ShutdownTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n        EnableHealthz:   true,\n        EnableReadyz:    true,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### router.go\n\n```go\ntype Router struct {\n    chi.Router\n}\n\nfunc NewRouter() *Router {\n    r := chi.NewRouter()\n    return &Router{Router: r}\n}\n\nfunc (r *Router) RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler) {\n    for _, h := range handlers {\n        h.Register(r.Router)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### handlers/handler.go\n\n```go\ntype Handler interface {\n    Register(r chi.Router)\n}\n\ntype HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n\nfunc (hf HandlerFunc) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    if err := hf(w, r); err != nil {\n        HandleError(w, r, err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### handlers/health.go\n\n```go\ntype HealthChecker interface {\n    IsHealthy() bool\n    IsReady() bool\n}\n\ntype HealthHandler struct {\n    checker HealthChecker\n}\n\nfunc NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker) *HealthHandler {\n    return &HealthHandler{checker: checker}\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthHandler) Register(r chi.Router) {\n    r.Get(\"/healthz\", h.healthz)\n    r.Get(\"/readyz\", h.readyz)\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthHandler) healthz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthHandler) readyz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    if h.checker == nil || !h.checker.IsReady() {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n        json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"not ready\"})\n        return\n    }\n    w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n}\n```\n\n### middleware/logging.go\n\n```go\ntype LoggingMiddleware struct {\n    logger Logger\n}\n\nfunc NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger) *LoggingMiddleware {\n    return &LoggingMiddleware{logger: logger}\n}\n\ntype responseWriterWrapper struct {\n    http.ResponseWriter\n    status int\n}\n\nfunc (w *responseWriterWrapper) WriteHeader(code int) {\n    w.status = code\n    w.ResponseWriter.WriteHeader(code)\n}\n\nfunc (m *LoggingMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        start := time.Now()\n        \n        ww := &responseWriterWrapper{ResponseWriter: w}\n        next.ServeHTTP(ww, r)\n        \n        m.logger.Info(\"request\",\n            \"method\", r.Method,\n            \"path\", r.URL.Path,\n            \"status\", ww.status,\n            \"duration\", time.Since(start),\n        )\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### middleware/recovery.go\n\n```go\ntype RecoveryMiddleware struct {\n    logger Logger\n}\n\nfunc NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger) *RecoveryMiddleware {\n    return &RecoveryMiddleware{logger: logger}\n}\n\nfunc (m *RecoveryMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        defer func() {\n            if err := recover(); err != nil {\n                m.logger.Error(\"panic recovered\", \"error\", err, \"path\", r.URL.Path)\n                http.Error(w, \"Internal Server Error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n            }\n        }()\n        next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### middleware/cors.go\n\n```go\ntype CORSConfig struct {\n    AllowedOrigins   []string\n    AllowedMethods   []string\n    AllowedHeaders   []string\n    AllowCredentials bool\n}\n\ntype CORSMiddleware struct {\n    config CORSConfig\n}\n\nfunc NewCORSMiddleware(config CORSConfig) *CORSMiddleware {\n    return &CORSMiddleware{config: config}\n}\n\nfunc (m *CORSMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        origin := r.Header.Get(\"Origin\")\n        if origin != \"\" && m.isAllowedOrigin(origin) {\n            w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Origin\", origin)\n            w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Methods\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedMethods, \",\"))\n            w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Headers\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedHeaders, \",\"))\n            if m.config.AllowCredentials {\n                w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials\", \"true\")\n            }\n        }\n        \n        if r.Method == \"OPTIONS\" {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n            return\n        }\n        \n        next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n    })\n}\n\nfunc (m *CORSMiddleware) isAllowedOrigin(origin string) bool {\n    for _, o := range m.config.AllowedOrigins {\n        if o == \"*\" || o == origin {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n### types.go\n\n```go\ntype Logger interface {\n    Info(msg string, args ...any)\n    Error(msg string, args ...any)\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n    Details any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SuccessResponse struct {\n    Data any `json:\"data\"`\n}\n\ntype ValidationError struct {\n    Field   string\n    Reason  string\n}\n\nfunc (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"validation error: %s - %s\", e.Field, e.Reason)\n}\n\ntype NotFoundError struct {\n    Resource string\n    Name     string\n}\n\nfunc (e *NotFoundError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"not found: %s/%s\", e.Resource, e.Name)\n}\n\ntype InternalError struct {\n    Err error\n}\n\nfunc (e *InternalError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"internal error: %v\", e.Err)\n}\n\ntype ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n    Dependency string\n}\n\nfunc (e *ServiceUnavailableError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"service unavailable: %s\", e.Dependency)\n}\n\nfunc HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    \n    var resp ErrorResponse\n    var status int\n    \n    switch e := err.(type) {\n    case *ValidationError:\n        status = http.StatusBadRequest\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n            Message: \"Invalid request parameter\",\n            Details: map[string]string{\"field\": e.Field, \"reason\": e.Reason},\n        }\n    case *NotFoundError:\n        status = http.StatusNotFound\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"NOT_FOUND\",\n            Message: e.Error(),\n        }\n    case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n        status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\",\n            Message: e.Error(),\n        }\n    case *InternalError:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n            Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n        }\n    default:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n            Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n        }\n    }\n    \n    w.WriteHeader(status)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n}\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Response |\n|----------|--------|---------|----------|\n| `/healthz` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe | `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` (HTTP 200) |\n| `/readyz` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe | `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` (HTTP 200) or `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` (HTTP 503) |\n\n### Health Endpoint Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Scenario | Request | Expected Response |\n|----------|---------|-------------------|\n| healthz always OK | GET /healthz | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n| readyz with checker ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=true) | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n| readyz with checker not ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=false) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n| readyz without checker | GET /readyz (checker=nil) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n\n### API Group\n\n| Prefix | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `/api/v1` | 业务 API 路由组（待后续 AR 实现） |\n\n### Middleware Chain\n\n```\nRecovery → Logging → CORS (optional) → Business Handler\n```\n\n### Middleware Chain Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Scenario | Input | Expected Behavior |\n|----------|-------|-------------------|\n| Recovery catches panic | Handler panics | Recovery middleware catches panic before Logging logs |\n| Logging captures duration | Normal request | Logging captures full request duration including handler execution |\n| CORS optional | CORS not configured | CORS middleware NOT applied to chain |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Type Mapping\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Description |\n|------------|-------------|------------|-------------|\n| ValidationError | 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | Invalid request parameter |\n| NotFoundError | 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | Resource not found |\n| InternalError | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Unexpected server error |\n| ServiceUnavailableError | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | Dependency unavailable |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n统一错误响应格式:\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n  \"message\": \"Invalid request parameter\",\n  \"details\": {\"field\": \"name\", \"reason\": \"required\"}\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Expected Response |\n|----------|------------|-------------------|\n| Validation error | ValidationError | HTTP 400, `{\"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", ...}` |\n| Not found error | NotFoundError | HTTP 404, `{\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\", ...}` |\n| Internal error | InternalError | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n| Service unavailable | ServiceUnavailableError | HTTP 503, `{\"code\": \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}` |\n| Unknown error | any other | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n\n### Response Headers\n\nAll error responses MUST include:\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File | Test Category | Coverage Target |\n|-----------|---------------|-----------------|\n| `server_test.go` | HTTPServer 启动/关闭 | 测试优雅关闭逻辑、超时处理 |\n| `router_test.go` | Router 初始化/注册 | 测试 NewRouter、RegisterHandlers |\n| `types_test.go` | HandleError/响应类型 | 测试正确 JSON 格式和状态码 |\n| `handlers/health_test.go` | healthz/readyz | 测试 HTTP 200/503 响应 |\n| `middleware/logging_test.go` | 请求日志 | 测试 method/path/status 捕获 |\n| `middleware/recovery_test.go` | Panic 恢复 | 测试 HTTP 500 响应 |\n| `middleware/cors_test.go` | CORS 头 | 测试 Access-Control 头、OPTIONS 处理 |\n\n### Unit Test Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|-------------------|\n| NewHTTPServer | Returns server with router initialized using chi.NewRouter() |\n| HTTPServer.Start | Returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe |\n| HTTPServer.Stop | Calls Shutdown with context timeout, closes stopCh |\n| GracefulShutdown | Sets up SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers |\n| RegisterHandlers | Each handler's Register method called |\n| HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP | Calls handler, handles errors via HandleError |\n| healthz endpoint | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n| readyz endpoint (ready) | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n| readyz endpoint (not ready) | HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n| LoggingMiddleware.Wrap | Captures method, path, status, duration |\n| responseWriterWrapper.WriteHeader | Sets status code, calls embedded WriteHeader |\n| RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap | Recovers panic, returns HTTP 500 |\n| CORSMiddleware.Wrap | Adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header |\n| CORS OPTIONS request | HTTP 200 with preflight headers |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| End-to-end health check | 启动真实 HTTP 服务器，GET /healthz 返回 HTTP 200 |\n| End-to-end readiness check | 启动服务器，GET /readyz 返回匹配 HealthChecker 状态 |\n| Middleware chain verification | 验证中间件按正确顺序执行 |\n| Panic recovery in integration | 服务器不崩溃，返回 HTTP 500 |\n\n### Integration Test Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|-------------------|\n| E2E healthz | GET /healthz on running server → HTTP 200 with correct JSON |\n| E2E readyz | GET /readyz matches HealthChecker.IsReady() state |\n| Middleware order | Recovery → Logging → Handler executes correctly |\n| Panic recovery | Server does NOT crash, response is HTTP 500 |\n\n### Test Coverage Requirements\n\n| Requirement | Threshold |\n|-------------|-----------|\n| Overall coverage | > 80% |\n| Package coverage | > 80% per package |\n\n### Test File Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n  server_test.go\n  router_test.go\n  types_test.go\n  handlers/health_test.go\n  middleware/logging_test.go\n  middleware/recovery_test.go\n  middleware/cors_test.go\n  integration_test.go\n```\n\n### Code Quality Requirements\n\n| Check | Command | Expected |\n|-------|---------|----------|\n| go vet | `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n| golangci-lint | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n| go build | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Build succeeds |\n| go test | `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Coverage > 80% |\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n  server.go              — HTTPServer 实现\n  router.go              — Router 封装\n  config.go              — Config 结构体 + DefaultConfig\n  types.go               — ErrorResponse, SuccessResponse, HandleError, Logger, error types\n  doc.go                 — Package-level godoc\n  handlers/\n    handler.go           — Handler 接口 + HandlerFunc\n    health.go            — HealthHandler + HealthChecker\n  middleware/\n    logging.go           — LoggingMiddleware + responseWriterWrapper\n    recovery.go          — RecoveryMiddleware\n    cors.go              — CORSMiddleware + CORSConfig\n```\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] HTTPServer struct contains: server, router, config, handlers, logger, stopCh\n- [ ] Config struct contains: Addr, ReadTimeout, WriteTimeout, IdleTimeout, ShutdownTimeout, EnableHealthz, EnableReadyz\n- [ ] DefaultConfig returns: Addr \":8080\", ReadTimeout 15s, WriteTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 60s, ShutdownTimeout 30s\n- [ ] NewHTTPServer initializes router with chi.NewRouter()\n- [ ] HTTPServer.Start returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe\n- [ ] HTTPServer.Stop calls Shutdown with context timeout\n- [ ] HTTPServer.GracefulShutdown handles SIGTERM/SIGINT\n- [ ] Router struct embeds chi.Router\n- [ ] RegisterHandlers calls each handler's Register method\n- [ ] Handler interface defines Register(r chi.Router)\n- [ ] HandlerFunc type: func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n- [ ] HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP calls HandleError on error\n- [ ] RegisterHandler stores handler in map and registers on router\n- [ ] HealthChecker interface defines IsHealthy() and IsReady()\n- [ ] healthz endpoint returns HTTP 200 with {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n- [ ] readyz endpoint returns HTTP 200/503 based on checker state\n- [ ] LoggingMiddleware.Wrap captures method, path, status, duration\n- [ ] responseWriterWrapper captures status code\n- [ ] RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap catches panic, returns HTTP 500\n- [ ] CORSMiddleware.Wrap adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n- [ ] CORS OPTIONS request returns HTTP 200 with preflight headers\n- [ ] ErrorResponse struct: Code, Message, Details\n- [ ] SuccessResponse struct: Data\n- [ ] HandleError maps error types to HTTP status codes\n- [ ] HandleError sets Content-Type: application/json\n- [ ] Middleware chain: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Handler\n- [ ] Pass `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] Pass `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` with >80% coverage\n- [ ] All exported types have godoc comments\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- 是否需要 WebSocket 支持？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n- 是否需要限流中间件？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n- 日志库选型：pkg/logging 还是第三方（如 zap、logrus）？\n- 指标端点 `/metrics` 是否在本 AR 范围内？（建议预留路由，实现待后续 AR）\n\n## References\n\n- chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n- Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n- Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md","after":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，提供 RESTful API 基础设施、中间件架构、生命周期管理。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\ncmd/workload-manager/\n    └── main.go                    — 入口，调用 pkg/workloadmanager\npkg/workloadmanager/\n    ├── server.go                  — HTTPServer 核心实现\n    ├── router.go                  — 路由配置与路由组\n    ├── config.go                  — 配置结构体\n    ├── types.go                   — 公共类型定义\n    ├── doc.go                     — 包文档\n    ├── handlers/\n    │   ├── handler.go             — Handler 接口\n    │   └── health.go              — 健康检查实现\n    └── middleware/\n        ├── logging.go             — 请求日志中间件\n        ├── recovery.go            — Panic 恢复中间件\n        └── cors.go                — CORS 中间件\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Client Integration\n\nWorkloadManager 使用 `client-go` 与 Kubernetes API 交互:\n\n| Client | API Group | Resource | Purpose |\n|--------|-----------|----------|---------|\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `agentruntimes` | 管理 AgentRuntime CR |\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `codeinterpreters` | 管理 CodeInterpreter CR |\n\nClient construction pattern:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    versioned \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n)\n\nfunc NewKubernetesClient(config *rest.Config) (versioned.Interface, error) {\n    return versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n}\n```\n\nTyped client interfaces:\n\n```go\ntype RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n    CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `net/http` | 标准库 HTTP 服务器 |\n| `context` | 请求上下文 |\n| `sync` | 并发控制（优雅关闭） |\n| `os/signal` | 信号处理 |\n| `time` | 超时配置 |\n| `encoding/json` | JSON 序列化 |\n| `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP 路由器 |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/rest` | Kubernetes REST 配置 |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | 生成的 typed client |\n\n### Router Library Selection\n\n**决策**: 使用 `go-chi/chi` v5\n\n| Aspect | Rationale |\n|--------|-----------|\n| 零外部依赖 | 仅依赖 Go 标准库 |\n| 兼容 net/http | 可使用所有标准库中间件 |\n| 路由分组 | 支持路由组与中间件作用域 |\n| 性能 | 足够优秀（参考 benchmark） |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### server.go\n\n```go\ntype HTTPServer struct {\n    server   *http.Server\n    router   chi.Router\n    config   Config\n    handlers map[string]Handler\n    logger   Logger\n    stopCh   chan struct{}\n}\n\nfunc NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger) *HTTPServer {\n    return &HTTPServer{\n        server:   &http.Server{Addr: cfg.Addr},\n        router:   chi.NewRouter(),\n        config:   cfg,\n        handlers: make(map[string]Handler),\n        logger:   logger,\n        stopCh:   make(chan struct{}),\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) Start() <-chan error {\n    errCh := make(chan error, 1)\n    s.server.ReadTimeout = s.config.ReadTimeout\n    s.server.WriteTimeout = s.config.WriteTimeout\n    s.server.IdleTimeout = s.config.IdleTimeout\n    go func() {\n        if err := s.server.ListenAndServe(); err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n            errCh <- err\n        }\n    }()\n    return errCh\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) Stop(ctx context.Context) error {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, s.config.ShutdownTimeout)\n    defer cancel()\n    err := s.server.Shutdown(ctx)\n    close(s.stopCh)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) GracefulShutdown() {\n    sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n    go func() {\n        <-sigCh\n        ctx := context.Background()\n        s.Stop(ctx)\n    }()\n}\n\nfunc (s *HTTPServer) RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler) {\n    s.handlers[name] = h\n    h.Register(s.router)\n}\n```\n\n### config.go\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Addr              string        // 监听地址，如 \":8080\"\n    ReadTimeout       time.Duration // 读超时\n    WriteTimeout      time.Duration // 写超时\n    IdleTimeout       time.Duration // 空闲连接超时\n    ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration // 优雅关闭超时\n    EnableHealthz     bool          // 是否启用健康检查\n    EnableReadyz      bool          // 是否启用就绪探针\n}\n\nfunc DefaultConfig() Config {\n    return Config{\n        Addr:            \":8080\",\n        ReadTimeout:     15 * time.Second,\n        WriteTimeout:    15 * time.Second,\n        IdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n        ShutdownTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n        EnableHealthz:   true,\n        EnableReadyz:    true,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### router.go\n\n```go\ntype Router struct {\n    chi.Router\n}\n\nfunc NewRouter() *Router {\n    r := chi.NewRouter()\n    return &Router{Router: r}\n}\n\nfunc (r *Router) RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler) {\n    for _, h := range handlers {\n        h.Register(r.Router)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### handlers/handler.go\n\n```go\ntype Handler interface {\n    Register(r chi.Router)\n}\n\ntype HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n\nfunc (hf HandlerFunc) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    if err := hf(w, r); err != nil {\n        HandleError(w, r, err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### handlers/health.go\n\n```go\ntype HealthChecker interface {\n    IsHealthy() bool\n    IsReady() bool\n}\n\ntype HealthHandler struct {\n    checker HealthChecker\n}\n\nfunc NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker) *HealthHandler {\n    return &HealthHandler{checker: checker}\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthHandler) Register(r chi.Router) {\n    r.Get(\"/healthz\", h.healthz)\n    r.Get(\"/readyz\", h.readyz)\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthHandler) healthz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n}\n\nfunc (h *HealthHandler) readyz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    if h.checker == nil || !h.checker.IsReady() {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n        json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"not ready\"})\n        return\n    }\n    w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n}\n```\n\n### middleware/logging.go\n\n```go\ntype LoggingMiddleware struct {\n    logger Logger\n}\n\nfunc NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger) *LoggingMiddleware {\n    return &LoggingMiddleware{logger: logger}\n}\n\ntype responseWriterWrapper struct {\n    http.ResponseWriter\n    status int\n}\n\nfunc (w *responseWriterWrapper) WriteHeader(code int) {\n    w.status = code\n    w.ResponseWriter.WriteHeader(code)\n}\n\nfunc (m *LoggingMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        start := time.Now()\n        \n        ww := &responseWriterWrapper{ResponseWriter: w}\n        next.ServeHTTP(ww, r)\n        \n        m.logger.Info(\"request\",\n            \"method\", r.Method,\n            \"path\", r.URL.Path,\n            \"status\", ww.status,\n            \"duration\", time.Since(start),\n        )\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### middleware/recovery.go\n\n```go\ntype RecoveryMiddleware struct {\n    logger Logger\n}\n\nfunc NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger) *RecoveryMiddleware {\n    return &RecoveryMiddleware{logger: logger}\n}\n\nfunc (m *RecoveryMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        defer func() {\n            if err := recover(); err != nil {\n                m.logger.Error(\"panic recovered\", \"error\", err, \"path\", r.URL.Path)\n                http.Error(w, \"Internal Server Error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n            }\n        }()\n        next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### middleware/cors.go\n\n```go\ntype CORSConfig struct {\n    AllowedOrigins   []string\n    AllowedMethods   []string\n    AllowedHeaders   []string\n    AllowCredentials bool\n}\n\ntype CORSMiddleware struct {\n    config CORSConfig\n}\n\nfunc NewCORSMiddleware(config CORSConfig) *CORSMiddleware {\n    return &CORSMiddleware{config: config}\n}\n\nfunc (m *CORSMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        origin := r.Header.Get(\"Origin\")\n        if origin != \"\" && m.isAllowedOrigin(origin) {\n            w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Origin\", origin)\n            w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Methods\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedMethods, \",\"))\n            w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Headers\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedHeaders, \",\"))\n            if m.config.AllowCredentials {\n                w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials\", \"true\")\n            }\n        }\n        \n        if r.Method == \"OPTIONS\" {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n            return\n        }\n        \n        next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n    })\n}\n\nfunc (m *CORSMiddleware) isAllowedOrigin(origin string) bool {\n    for _, o := range m.config.AllowedOrigins {\n        if o == \"*\" || o == origin {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n### types.go\n\n```go\ntype Logger interface {\n    Info(msg string, args ...any)\n    Error(msg string, args ...any)\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n    Details any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SuccessResponse struct {\n    Data any `json:\"data\"`\n}\n\ntype ValidationError struct {\n    Field   string\n    Reason  string\n}\n\nfunc (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"validation error: %s - %s\", e.Field, e.Reason)\n}\n\ntype NotFoundError struct {\n    Resource string\n    Name     string\n}\n\nfunc (e *NotFoundError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"not found: %s/%s\", e.Resource, e.Name)\n}\n\ntype InternalError struct {\n    Err error\n}\n\nfunc (e *InternalError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"internal error: %v\", e.Err)\n}\n\ntype ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n    Dependency string\n}\n\nfunc (e *ServiceUnavailableError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"service unavailable: %s\", e.Dependency)\n}\n\nfunc HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    \n    var resp ErrorResponse\n    var status int\n    \n    switch e := err.(type) {\n    case *ValidationError:\n        status = http.StatusBadRequest\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n            Message: \"Invalid request parameter\",\n            Details: map[string]string{\"field\": e.Field, \"reason\": e.Reason},\n        }\n    case *NotFoundError:\n        status = http.StatusNotFound\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"NOT_FOUND\",\n            Message: e.Error(),\n        }\n    case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n        status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\",\n            Message: e.Error(),\n        }\n    case *InternalError:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n            Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n        }\n    default:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        resp = ErrorResponse{\n            Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n            Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n        }\n    }\n    \n    w.WriteHeader(status)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n}\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Response |\n|----------|--------|---------|----------|\n| `/healthz` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe | `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` (HTTP 200) |\n| `/readyz` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe | `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` (HTTP 200) or `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` (HTTP 503) |\n\n### Health Endpoint Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Scenario | Request | Expected Response |\n|----------|---------|-------------------|\n| healthz always OK | GET /healthz | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n| readyz with checker ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=true) | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n| readyz with checker not ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=false) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n| readyz without checker | GET /readyz (checker=nil) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n\n### API Group\n\n| Prefix | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `/api/v1` | 业务 API 路由组（待后续 AR 实现） |\n\n### Middleware Chain\n\n```\nRecovery → Logging → CORS (optional) → Business Handler\n```\n\n### Middleware Chain Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Scenario | Input | Expected Behavior |\n|----------|-------|-------------------|\n| Recovery catches panic | Handler panics | Recovery middleware catches panic before Logging logs |\n| Logging captures duration | Normal request | Logging captures full request duration including handler execution |\n| CORS optional | CORS not configured | CORS middleware NOT applied to chain |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Type Mapping\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Description |\n|------------|-------------|------------|-------------|\n| ValidationError | 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | Invalid request parameter |\n| NotFoundError | 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | Resource not found |\n| InternalError | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Unexpected server error |\n| ServiceUnavailableError | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | Dependency unavailable |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n统一错误响应格式:\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n  \"message\": \"Invalid request parameter\",\n  \"details\": {\"field\": \"name\", \"reason\": \"required\"}\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Expected Response |\n|----------|------------|-------------------|\n| Validation error | ValidationError | HTTP 400, `{\"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", ...}` |\n| Not found error | NotFoundError | HTTP 404, `{\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\", ...}` |\n| Internal error | InternalError | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n| Service unavailable | ServiceUnavailableError | HTTP 503, `{\"code\": \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}` |\n| Unknown error | any other | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n\n### Response Headers\n\nAll error responses MUST include:\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File | Test Category | Coverage Target |\n|-----------|---------------|-----------------|\n| `server_test.go` | HTTPServer 启动/关闭 | 测试优雅关闭逻辑、超时处理 |\n| `router_test.go` | Router 初始化/注册 | 测试 NewRouter、RegisterHandlers |\n| `types_test.go` | HandleError/响应类型 | 测试正确 JSON 格式和状态码 |\n| `handlers/health_test.go` | healthz/readyz | 测试 HTTP 200/503 响应 |\n| `middleware/logging_test.go` | 请求日志 | 测试 method/path/status 捕获 |\n| `middleware/recovery_test.go` | Panic 恢复 | 测试 HTTP 500 响应 |\n| `middleware/cors_test.go` | CORS 头 | 测试 Access-Control 头、OPTIONS 处理 |\n\n### Unit Test Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|-------------------|\n| NewHTTPServer | Returns server with router initialized using chi.NewRouter() |\n| HTTPServer.Start | Returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe |\n| HTTPServer.Stop | Calls Shutdown with context timeout, closes stopCh |\n| GracefulShutdown | Sets up SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers |\n| RegisterHandlers | Each handler's Register method called |\n| HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP | Calls handler, handles errors via HandleError |\n| healthz endpoint | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n| readyz endpoint (ready) | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n| readyz endpoint (not ready) | HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n| LoggingMiddleware.Wrap | Captures method, path, status, duration |\n| responseWriterWrapper.WriteHeader | Sets status code, calls embedded WriteHeader |\n| RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap | Recovers panic, returns HTTP 500 |\n| CORSMiddleware.Wrap | Adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header |\n| CORS OPTIONS request | HTTP 200 with preflight headers |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| End-to-end health check | 启动真实 HTTP 服务器，GET /healthz 返回 HTTP 200 |\n| End-to-end readiness check | 启动服务器，GET /readyz 返回匹配 HealthChecker 状态 |\n| Middleware chain verification | 验证中间件按正确顺序执行 |\n| Panic recovery in integration | 服务器不崩溃，返回 HTTP 500 |\n\n### Integration Test Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|-------------------|\n| E2E healthz | GET /healthz on running server → HTTP 200 with correct JSON |\n| E2E readyz | GET /readyz matches HealthChecker.IsReady() state |\n| Middleware order | Recovery → Logging → Handler executes correctly |\n| Panic recovery | Server does NOT crash, response is HTTP 500 |\n\n### Test Coverage Requirements\n\n| Requirement | Threshold |\n|-------------|-----------|\n| Overall coverage | > 80% |\n| Package coverage | > 80% per package |\n\n### Test File Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n  server_test.go\n  router_test.go\n  types_test.go\n  handlers/health_test.go\n  middleware/logging_test.go\n  middleware/recovery_test.go\n  middleware/cors_test.go\n  integration_test.go\n```\n\n### Code Quality Requirements\n\n| Check | Command | Expected |\n|-------|---------|----------|\n| go vet | `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n| golangci-lint | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n| go build | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Build succeeds |\n| go test | `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Coverage > 80% |\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n  server.go              — HTTPServer 实现\n  router.go              — Router 封装\n  config.go              — Config 结构体 + DefaultConfig\n  types.go               — ErrorResponse, SuccessResponse, HandleError, Logger, error types\n  doc.go                 — Package-level godoc\n  handlers/\n    handler.go           — Handler 接口 + HandlerFunc\n    health.go            — HealthHandler + HealthChecker\n  middleware/\n    logging.go           — LoggingMiddleware + responseWriterWrapper\n    recovery.go          — RecoveryMiddleware\n    cors.go              — CORSMiddleware + CORSConfig\n```\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] HTTPServer struct contains: server, router, config, handlers, logger, stopCh\n- [ ] Config struct contains: Addr, ReadTimeout, WriteTimeout, IdleTimeout, ShutdownTimeout, EnableHealthz, EnableReadyz\n- [ ] DefaultConfig returns: Addr \":8080\", ReadTimeout 15s, WriteTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 60s, ShutdownTimeout 30s\n- [ ] NewHTTPServer initializes router with chi.NewRouter()\n- [ ] HTTPServer.Start returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe\n- [ ] HTTPServer.Stop calls Shutdown with context timeout\n- [ ] HTTPServer.GracefulShutdown handles SIGTERM/SIGINT\n- [ ] Router struct embeds chi.Router\n- [ ] RegisterHandlers calls each handler's Register method\n- [ ] Handler interface defines Register(r chi.Router)\n- [ ] HandlerFunc type: func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n- [ ] HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP calls HandleError on error\n- [ ] RegisterHandler stores handler in map and registers on router\n- [ ] HealthChecker interface defines IsHealthy() and IsReady()\n- [ ] healthz endpoint returns HTTP 200 with {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n- [ ] readyz endpoint returns HTTP 200/503 based on checker state\n- [ ] LoggingMiddleware.Wrap captures method, path, status, duration\n- [ ] responseWriterWrapper captures status code\n- [ ] RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap catches panic, returns HTTP 500\n- [ ] CORSMiddleware.Wrap adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n- [ ] CORS OPTIONS request returns HTTP 200 with preflight headers\n- [ ] ErrorResponse struct: Code, Message, Details\n- [ ] SuccessResponse struct: Data\n- [ ] HandleError maps error types to HTTP status codes\n- [ ] HandleError sets Content-Type: application/json\n- [ ] Middleware chain: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Handler\n- [ ] Pass `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] Pass `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` with >80% coverage\n- [ ] All exported types have godoc comments\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- 是否需要 WebSocket 支持？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n- 是否需要限流中间件？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n- 日志库选型：pkg/logging 还是第三方（如 zap、logrus）？\n- 指标端点 `/metrics` 是否在本 AR 范围内？（建议预留路由，实现待后续 AR）\n\n## References\n\n- chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n- Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n- Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- client-go: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n- AgentRuntime types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n- CodeInterpreter types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- Shared types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n- AR-003 Design: `changes/AR-003/design.md`","additions":6,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md","time":{"start":1775842084816,"end":1775842084830}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775842084866,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786fc7e3001YZIUa2u45FaxHm","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d786fa8e50011gOp6IZ9ulC6t3","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":54793,"input":825,"output":273,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":53695}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775842087749,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786fd3430010yF6s2iO4dc5V2","messageID":"msg_d786fc81f0015CxHE5afzgm3Bg","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842088932,"sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","part":{"id":"prt_d786fd7c10017RhMtU0cWkbHDe","messageID":"msg_d786fc81f0015CxHE5afzgm3Bg","sessionID":"ses_28793b96fffeRkvD3Rh6IUMx22","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1b4aba28216448cebd62740e1815ba20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，提供 RESTful API 基础设施、中间件架构、生命周期管理。\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: cmd/workload-manager/\n21:     └── main.go                    — 入口，调用 pkg/workloadmanager\n22: pkg/workloadmanager/\n23:     ├── server.go                  — HTTPServer 核心实现\n24:     ├── router.go                  — 路由配置与路由组\n25:     ├── config.go                  — 配置结构体\n26:     ├── types.go                   — 公共类型定义\n27:     ├── doc.go                     — 包文档\n28:     ├── handlers/\n29:     │   ├── handler.go             — Handler 接口\n30:     │   └── health.go              — 健康检查实现\n31:     └── middleware/\n32:         ├── logging.go             — 请求日志中间件\n33:         ├── recovery.go            — Panic 恢复中间件\n34:         └── cors.go                — CORS 中间件\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Kubernetes Client Integration\n38: \n39: WorkloadManager 使用 `client-go` 与 Kubernetes API 交互:\n40: \n41: | Client | API Group | Resource | Purpose |\n42: |--------|-----------|----------|---------|\n43: | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `agentruntimes` | 管理 AgentRuntime CR |\n44: | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` | `codeinterpreters` | 管理 CodeInterpreter CR |\n45: \n46: Client construction pattern:\n47: \n48: ```go\n49: import (\n50:     versioned \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n51:     \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n52: )\n53: \n54: func NewKubernetesClient(config *rest.Config) (versioned.Interface, error) {\n55:     return versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n56: }\n57: ```\n58: \n59: Typed client interfaces:\n60: \n61: ```go\n62: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n63:     RESTClient() rest.Interface\n64:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n65:     CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n66: }\n67: \n68: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n69:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n70:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n71:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n72:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n73:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n74:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n75:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n76:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n77: }\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Dependencies\n81: \n82: | Package | Purpose |\n83: |---------|---------|\n84: | `net/http` | 标准库 HTTP 服务器 |\n85: | `context` | 请求上下文 |\n86: | `sync` | 并发控制（优雅关闭） |\n87: | `os/signal` | 信号处理 |\n88: | `time` | 超时配置 |\n89: | `encoding/json` | JSON 序列化 |\n90: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP 路由器 |\n91: | `k8s.io/client-go/rest` | Kubernetes REST 配置 |\n92: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | 生成的 typed client |\n93: \n94: ### Router Library Selection\n95: \n96: **决策**: 使用 `go-chi/chi` v5\n97: \n98: | Aspect | Rationale |\n99: |--------|-----------|\n100: | 零外部依赖 | 仅依赖 Go 标准库 |\n101: | 兼容 net/http | 可使用所有标准库中间件 |\n102: | 路由分组 | 支持路由组与中间件作用域 |\n103: | 性能 | 足够优秀（参考 benchmark） |\n104: \n105: ## Data Structures\n106: \n107: ### server.go\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: type HTTPServer struct {\n111:     server   *http.Server\n112:     router   chi.Router\n113:     config   Config\n114:     handlers map[string]Handler\n115:     logger   Logger\n116:     stopCh   chan struct{}\n117: }\n118: \n119: func NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger) *HTTPServer {\n120:     return &HTTPServer{\n121:         server:   &http.Server{Addr: cfg.Addr},\n122:         router:   chi.NewRouter(),\n123:         config:   cfg,\n124:         handlers: make(map[string]Handler),\n125:         logger:   logger,\n126:         stopCh:   make(chan struct{}),\n127:     }\n128: }\n129: \n130: func (s *HTTPServer) Start() <-chan error {\n131:     errCh := make(chan error, 1)\n132:     s.server.ReadTimeout = s.config.ReadTimeout\n133:     s.server.WriteTimeout = s.config.WriteTimeout\n134:     s.server.IdleTimeout = s.config.IdleTimeout\n135:     go func() {\n136:         if err := s.server.ListenAndServe(); err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n137:             errCh <- err\n138:         }\n139:     }()\n140:     return errCh\n141: }\n142: \n143: func (s *HTTPServer) Stop(ctx context.Context) error {\n144:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, s.config.ShutdownTimeout)\n145:     defer cancel()\n146:     err := s.server.Shutdown(ctx)\n147:     close(s.stopCh)\n148:     return err\n149: }\n150: \n151: func (s *HTTPServer) GracefulShutdown() {\n152:     sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n153:     signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n154:     go func() {\n155:         <-sigCh\n156:         ctx := context.Background()\n157:         s.Stop(ctx)\n158:     }()\n159: }\n160: \n161: func (s *HTTPServer) RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler) {\n162:     s.handlers[name] = h\n163:     h.Register(s.router)\n164: }\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ### config.go\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: type Config struct {\n171:     Addr              string        // 监听地址，如 \":8080\"\n172:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration // 读超时\n173:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration // 写超时\n174:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration // 空闲连接超时\n175:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration // 优雅关闭超时\n176:     EnableHealthz     bool          // 是否启用健康检查\n177:     EnableReadyz      bool          // 是否启用就绪探针\n178: }\n179: \n180: func DefaultConfig() Config {\n181:     return Config{\n182:         Addr:            \":8080\",\n183:         ReadTimeout:     15 * time.Second,\n184:         WriteTimeout:    15 * time.Second,\n185:         IdleTimeout:     60 * time.Second,\n186:         ShutdownTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n187:         EnableHealthz:   true,\n188:         EnableReadyz:    true,\n189:     }\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### router.go\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: type Router struct {\n197:     chi.Router\n198: }\n199: \n200: func NewRouter() *Router {\n201:     r := chi.NewRouter()\n202:     return &Router{Router: r}\n203: }\n204: \n205: func (r *Router) RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler) {\n206:     for _, h := range handlers {\n207:         h.Register(r.Router)\n208:     }\n209: }\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### handlers/handler.go\n213: \n214: ```go\n215: type Handler interface {\n216:     Register(r chi.Router)\n217: }\n218: \n219: type HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n220: \n221: func (hf HandlerFunc) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n222:     if err := hf(w, r); err != nil {\n223:         HandleError(w, r, err)\n224:     }\n225: }\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ### handlers/health.go\n229: \n230: ```go\n231: type HealthChecker interface {\n232:     IsHealthy() bool\n233:     IsReady() bool\n234: }\n235: \n236: type HealthHandler struct {\n237:     checker HealthChecker\n238: }\n239: \n240: func NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker) *HealthHandler {\n241:     return &HealthHandler{checker: checker}\n242: }\n243: \n244: func (h *HealthHandler) Register(r chi.Router) {\n245:     r.Get(\"/healthz\", h.healthz)\n246:     r.Get(\"/readyz\", h.readyz)\n247: }\n248: \n249: func (h *HealthHandler) healthz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n250:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n251:     w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n252:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n253: }\n254: \n255: func (h *HealthHandler) readyz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n256:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n257:     if h.checker == nil || !h.checker.IsReady() {\n258:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n259:         json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"not ready\"})\n260:         return\n261:     }\n262:     w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n263:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n264: }\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ### middleware/logging.go\n268: \n269: ```go\n270: type LoggingMiddleware struct {\n271:     logger Logger\n272: }\n273: \n274: func NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger) *LoggingMiddleware {\n275:     return &LoggingMiddleware{logger: logger}\n276: }\n277: \n278: type responseWriterWrapper struct {\n279:     http.ResponseWriter\n280:     status int\n281: }\n282: \n283: func (w *responseWriterWrapper) WriteHeader(code int) {\n284:     w.status = code\n285:     w.ResponseWriter.WriteHeader(code)\n286: }\n287: \n288: func (m *LoggingMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n289:     return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n290:         start := time.Now()\n291:         \n292:         ww := &responseWriterWrapper{ResponseWriter: w}\n293:         next.ServeHTTP(ww, r)\n294:         \n295:         m.logger.Info(\"request\",\n296:             \"method\", r.Method,\n297:             \"path\", r.URL.Path,\n298:             \"status\", ww.status,\n299:             \"duration\", time.Since(start),\n300:         )\n301:     })\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ### middleware/recovery.go\n306: \n307: ```go\n308: type RecoveryMiddleware struct {\n309:     logger Logger\n310: }\n311: \n312: func NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger) *RecoveryMiddleware {\n313:     return &RecoveryMiddleware{logger: logger}\n314: }\n315: \n316: func (m *RecoveryMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n317:     return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n318:         defer func() {\n319:             if err := recover(); err != nil {\n320:                 m.logger.Error(\"panic recovered\", \"error\", err, \"path\", r.URL.Path)\n321:                 http.Error(w, \"Internal Server Error\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n322:             }\n323:         }()\n324:         next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n325:     })\n326: }\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ### middleware/cors.go\n330: \n331: ```go\n332: type CORSConfig struct {\n333:     AllowedOrigins   []string\n334:     AllowedMethods   []string\n335:     AllowedHeaders   []string\n336:     AllowCredentials bool\n337: }\n338: \n339: type CORSMiddleware struct {\n340:     config CORSConfig\n341: }\n342: \n343: func NewCORSMiddleware(config CORSConfig) *CORSMiddleware {\n344:     return &CORSMiddleware{config: config}\n345: }\n346: \n347: func (m *CORSMiddleware) Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n348:     return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n349:         origin := r.Header.Get(\"Origin\")\n350:         if origin != \"\" && m.isAllowedOrigin(origin) {\n351:             w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Origin\", origin)\n352:             w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Methods\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedMethods, \",\"))\n353:             w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Headers\", strings.Join(m.config.AllowedHeaders, \",\"))\n354:             if m.config.AllowCredentials {\n355:                 w.Header().Set(\"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials\", \"true\")\n356:             }\n357:         }\n358:         \n359:         if r.Method == \"OPTIONS\" {\n360:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n361:             return\n362:         }\n363:         \n364:         next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n365:     })\n366: }\n367: \n368: func (m *CORSMiddleware) isAllowedOrigin(origin string) bool {\n369:     for _, o := range m.config.AllowedOrigins {\n370:         if o == \"*\" || o == origin {\n371:             return true\n372:         }\n373:     }\n374:     return false\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### types.go\n379: \n380: ```go\n381: type Logger interface {\n382:     Info(msg string, args ...any)\n383:     Error(msg string, args ...any)\n384: }\n385: \n386: type ErrorResponse struct {\n387:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n388:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n389:     Details any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n390: }\n391: \n392: type SuccessResponse struct {\n393:     Data any `json:\"data\"`\n394: }\n395: \n396: type ValidationError struct {\n397:     Field   string\n398:     Reason  string\n399: }\n400: \n401: func (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n402:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"validation error: %s - %s\", e.Field, e.Reason)\n403: }\n404: \n405: type NotFoundError struct {\n406:     Resource string\n407:     Name     string\n408: }\n409: \n410: func (e *NotFoundError) Error() string {\n411:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"not found: %s/%s\", e.Resource, e.Name)\n412: }\n413: \n414: type InternalError struct {\n415:     Err error\n416: }\n417: \n418: func (e *InternalError) Error() string {\n419:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"internal error: %v\", e.Err)\n420: }\n421: \n422: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n423:     Dependency string\n424: }\n425: \n426: func (e *ServiceUnavailableError) Error() string {\n427:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"service unavailable: %s\", e.Dependency)\n428: }\n429: \n430: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request, err error) {\n431:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n432:     \n433:     var resp ErrorResponse\n434:     var status int\n435:     \n436:     switch e := err.(type) {\n437:     case *ValidationError:\n438:         status = http.StatusBadRequest\n439:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n440:             Code:    \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n441:             Message: \"Invalid request parameter\",\n442:             Details: map[string]string{\"field\": e.Field, \"reason\": e.Reason},\n443:         }\n444:     case *NotFoundError:\n445:         status = http.StatusNotFound\n446:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n447:             Code:    \"NOT_FOUND\",\n448:             Message: e.Error(),\n449:         }\n450:     case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n451:         status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n452:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n453:             Code:    \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\",\n454:             Message: e.Error(),\n455:         }\n456:     case *InternalError:\n457:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n458:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n459:             Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n460:             Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n461:         }\n462:     default:\n463:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n464:         resp = ErrorResponse{\n465:             Code:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n466:             Message: \"Unexpected server error\",\n467:         }\n468:     }\n469:     \n470:     w.WriteHeader(status)\n471:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ## API Endpoints\n476: \n477: ### Health Endpoints\n478: \n479: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Response |\n480: |----------|--------|---------|----------|\n481: | `/healthz` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe | `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` (HTTP 200) |\n482: | `/readyz` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe | `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` (HTTP 200) or `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` (HTTP 503) |\n483: \n484: ### Health Endpoint Acceptance Criteria\n485: \n486: | Scenario | Request | Expected Response |\n487: |----------|---------|-------------------|\n488: | healthz always OK | GET /healthz | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n489: | readyz with checker ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=true) | HTTP 200, `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n490: | readyz with checker not ready | GET /readyz (checker.IsReady()=false) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n491: | readyz without checker | GET /readyz (checker=nil) | HTTP 503, `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n492: \n493: ### API Group\n494: \n495: | Prefix | Purpose |\n496: |--------|---------|\n497: | `/api/v1` | 业务 API 路由组（待后续 AR 实现） |\n498: \n499: ### Middleware Chain\n500: \n501: ```\n502: Recovery → Logging → CORS (optional) → Business Handler\n503: ```\n504: \n505: ### Middleware Chain Acceptance Criteria\n506: \n507: | Scenario | Input | Expected Behavior |\n508: |----------|-------|-------------------|\n509: | Recovery catches panic | Handler panics | Recovery middleware catches panic before Logging logs |\n510: | Logging captures duration | Normal request | Logging captures full request duration including handler execution |\n511: | CORS optional | CORS not configured | CORS middleware NOT applied to chain |\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Type Mapping\n516: \n517: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Description |\n518: |------------|-------------|------------|-------------|\n519: | ValidationError | 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | Invalid request parameter |\n520: | NotFoundError | 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | Resource not found |\n521: | InternalError | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Unexpected server error |\n522: | ServiceUnavailableError | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | Dependency unavailable |\n523: \n524: ### Error Response Format\n525: \n526: 统一错误响应格式:\n527: ```json\n528: {\n529:   \"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n530:   \"message\": \"Invalid request parameter\",\n531:   \"details\": {\"field\": \"name\", \"reason\": \"required\"}\n532: }\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Error Handling Acceptance Criteria\n536: \n537: | Scenario | Error Type | Expected Response |\n538: |----------|------------|-------------------|\n539: | Validation error | ValidationError | HTTP 400, `{\"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", ...}` |\n540: | Not found error | NotFoundError | HTTP 404, `{\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\", ...}` |\n541: | Internal error | InternalError | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n542: | Service unavailable | ServiceUnavailableError | HTTP 503, `{\"code\": \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}` |\n543: | Unknown error | any other | HTTP 500, `{\"code\": \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", ...}` |\n544: \n545: ### Response Headers\n546: \n547: All error responses MUST include:\n548: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n549: \n550: ## Testing Strategy\n551: \n552: ### Unit Tests\n553: \n554: | Test File | Test Category | Coverage Target |\n555: |-----------|---------------|-----------------|\n556: | `server_test.go` | HTTPServer 启动/关闭 | 测试优雅关闭逻辑、超时处理 |\n557: | `router_test.go` | Router 初始化/注册 | 测试 NewRouter、RegisterHandlers |\n558: | `types_test.go` | HandleError/响应类型 | 测试正确 JSON 格式和状态码 |\n559: | `handlers/health_test.go` | healthz/readyz | 测试 HTTP 200/503 响应 |\n560: | `middleware/logging_test.go` | 请求日志 | 测试 method/path/status 捕获 |\n561: | `middleware/recovery_test.go` | Panic 恢复 | 测试 HTTP 500 响应 |\n562: | `middleware/cors_test.go` | CORS 头 | 测试 Access-Control 头、OPTIONS 处理 |\n563: \n564: ### Unit Test Acceptance Criteria\n565: \n566: | Test | Expected Behavior |\n567: |------|-------------------|\n568: | NewHTTPServer | Returns server with router initialized using chi.NewRouter() |\n569: | HTTPServer.Start | Returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe |\n570: | HTTPServer.Stop | Calls Shutdown with context timeout, closes stopCh |\n571: | GracefulShutdown | Sets up SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers |\n572: | RegisterHandlers | Each handler's Register method called |\n573: | HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP | Calls handler, handles errors via HandleError |\n574: | healthz endpoint | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` |\n575: | readyz endpoint (ready) | HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` |\n576: | readyz endpoint (not ready) | HTTP 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\"}` |\n577: | LoggingMiddleware.Wrap | Captures method, path, status, duration |\n578: | responseWriterWrapper.WriteHeader | Sets status code, calls embedded WriteHeader |\n579: | RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap | Recovers panic, returns HTTP 500 |\n580: | CORSMiddleware.Wrap | Adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header |\n581: | CORS OPTIONS request | HTTP 200 with preflight headers |\n582: \n583: ### Integration Tests\n584: \n585: | Test | Description |\n586: |------|-------------|\n587: | End-to-end health check | 启动真实 HTTP 服务器，GET /healthz 返回 HTTP 200 |\n588: | End-to-end readiness check | 启动服务器，GET /readyz 返回匹配 HealthChecker 状态 |\n589: | Middleware chain verification | 验证中间件按正确顺序执行 |\n590: | Panic recovery in integration | 服务器不崩溃，返回 HTTP 500 |\n591: \n592: ### Integration Test Acceptance Criteria\n593: \n594: | Test | Expected Behavior |\n595: |------|-------------------|\n596: | E2E healthz | GET /healthz on running server → HTTP 200 with correct JSON |\n597: | E2E readyz | GET /readyz matches HealthChecker.IsReady() state |\n598: | Middleware order | Recovery → Logging → Handler executes correctly |\n599: | Panic recovery | Server does NOT crash, response is HTTP 500 |\n600: \n601: ### Test Coverage Requirements\n602: \n603: | Requirement | Threshold |\n604: |-------------|-----------|\n605: | Overall coverage | > 80% |\n606: | Package coverage | > 80% per package |\n607: \n608: ### Test File Structure\n609: \n610: ```\n611: pkg/workloadmanager/\n612:   server_test.go\n613:   router_test.go\n614:   types_test.go\n615:   handlers/health_test.go\n616:   middleware/logging_test.go\n617:   middleware/recovery_test.go\n618:   middleware/cors_test.go\n619:   integration_test.go\n620: ```\n621: \n622: ### Code Quality Requirements\n623: \n624: | Check | Command | Expected |\n625: |-------|---------|----------|\n626: | go vet | `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n627: | golangci-lint | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Zero issues |\n628: | go build | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Build succeeds |\n629: | go test | `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` | Coverage > 80% |\n630: \n631: ## File Structure\n632: \n633: ```\n634: pkg/workloadmanager/\n635:   server.go              — HTTPServer 实现\n636:   router.go              — Router 封装\n637:   config.go              — Config 结构体 + DefaultConfig\n638:   types.go               — ErrorResponse, SuccessResponse, HandleError, Logger, error types\n639:   doc.go                 — Package-level godoc\n640:   handlers/\n641:     handler.go           — Handler 接口 + HandlerFunc\n642:     health.go            — HealthHandler + HealthChecker\n643:   middleware/\n644:     logging.go           — LoggingMiddleware + responseWriterWrapper\n645:     recovery.go          — RecoveryMiddleware\n646:     cors.go              — CORSMiddleware + CORSConfig\n647: ```\n648: \n649: ## Validation Checklist\n650: \n651: - [ ] HTTPServer struct contains: server, router, config, handlers, logger, stopCh\n652: - [ ] Config struct contains: Addr, ReadTimeout, WriteTimeout, IdleTimeout, ShutdownTimeout, EnableHealthz, EnableReadyz\n653: - [ ] DefaultConfig returns: Addr \":8080\", ReadTimeout 15s, WriteTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 60s, ShutdownTimeout 30s\n654: - [ ] NewHTTPServer initializes router with chi.NewRouter()\n655: - [ ] HTTPServer.Start returns error channel, starts ListenAndServe\n656: - [ ] HTTPServer.Stop calls Shutdown with context timeout\n657: - [ ] HTTPServer.GracefulShutdown handles SIGTERM/SIGINT\n658: - [ ] Router struct embeds chi.Router\n659: - [ ] RegisterHandlers calls each handler's Register method\n660: - [ ] Handler interface defines Register(r chi.Router)\n661: - [ ] HandlerFunc type: func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n662: - [ ] HandlerFunc.ServeHTTP calls HandleError on error\n663: - [ ] RegisterHandler stores handler in map and registers on router\n664: - [ ] HealthChecker interface defines IsHealthy() and IsReady()\n665: - [ ] healthz endpoint returns HTTP 200 with {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n666: - [ ] readyz endpoint returns HTTP 200/503 based on checker state\n667: - [ ] LoggingMiddleware.Wrap captures method, path, status, duration\n668: - [ ] responseWriterWrapper captures status code\n669: - [ ] RecoveryMiddleware.Wrap catches panic, returns HTTP 500\n670: - [ ] CORSMiddleware.Wrap adds Access-Control-Allow-Origin header\n671: - [ ] CORS OPTIONS request returns HTTP 200 with preflight headers\n672: - [ ] ErrorResponse struct: Code, Message, Details\n673: - [ ] SuccessResponse struct: Data\n674: - [ ] HandleError maps error types to HTTP status codes\n675: - [ ] HandleError sets Content-Type: application/json\n676: - [ ] Middleware chain: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Handler\n677: - [ ] Pass `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n678: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n679: - [ ] Pass `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` with >80% coverage\n680: - [ ] All exported types have godoc comments\n681: \n682: ## Open Questions\n683: \n684: - 是否需要 WebSocket 支持？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n685: - 是否需要限流中间件？（暂不在范围内，待后续 AR）\n686: - 日志库选型：pkg/logging 还是第三方（如 zap、logrus）？\n687: - 指标端点 `/metrics` 是否在本 AR 范围内？（建议预留路由，实现待后续 AR）\n688: \n689: ## References\n690: \n691: - chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n692: - Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n693: - Kubernetes API conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n694: - client-go: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n695: - AgentRuntime types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n696: - CodeInterpreter types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n697: - Shared types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n698: - AR-003 Design: `changes/AR-003/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 698 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n定义 WorkloadManager 的 HTTP 服务框架，提供 RESTful API 基础设施、中间件架构、生命周期管理。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\ncmd/workload-manager/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/design.md","time":{"start":1775842088921,"end":1775842088929}}}}
